  Locus:
    Page: 68
    Verse: 12
Tags:
  - Consciousness
---
Little ought you to care who you are; the urgent thing is what you will be.
The being that you are is but an unstable, perishable being, which eats of
the earth and which the earth some day will eat; what you will be is an
idea of you in God, the Consciousness of the universe.
